FLORA OF SOUTH CAROLINA
Lexington                    County

*Galax aphylla* L.
Steep north to east facing escarpment
and bluff dominated by *Kalmia*; some
ironstone exposed at bluff tip;
Vaucluse loamy sand; 1.7 miles due
ENE of the jct. of SC 6 and SR 162.
Gaston Quad, Lexington Soil Survey
Sheets 54 and 60.

Douglas A. Rayner #1163
14 February 1980
